        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and prove the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the flour, yeast, salt, and sugar. Add the melted butter, egg, and warm milk and mix to a soft dough. Knead for 5 minutes until smooth. Cover and leave for 30 minutes to rise slightly; the dough will not double but should feel noticeably puffed.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the caramel syrup",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the butter in a saucepan, add the brown sugar, golden syrup, and cinnamon. Stir over medium heat until the sugar dissolves and the mixture is smooth and thick. Keep warm over very low heat while you bake the waffles.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake and fill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat a round waffle iron. Divide the dough into 36 balls of about 20 g each. Roll each ball into a round slightly smaller than the waffle iron. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes per waffle until golden brown. Work immediately: split each hot waffle through the middle horizontally with a sharp knife, spread one side with a generous teaspoon of caramel syrup, and press the two halves together firmly. Set aside on a rack to cool. Work quickly; waffles become brittle within 2 minutes of coming off the iron.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
